'''African feminism''' is an important strain of feminism that is innovated by African women about the conditions of continental African women. It includes such forms as motherism, femalism, snail-sense feminism, and so on.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nkealah|first=Naomi|title=(West) African Feminisms and Their Challenges|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/pdf/10.1080/02564718.2016.1198156|journal=Journal of Literary Studies|volume=32|issue=2|pages=61â€“74|doi=10.1080/02564718.2016.1198156}}</ref>

